Akshay Kumar grooves to new version of Tu Cheez Badi Hai Mast Mast. See pics and video 
7-3-2017 
Bollywood actor Akshay Kumar has said his hit song, Tu Cheez Badi Hai Mast Mast from Mohra, played in important part in taking shaping up his career. “In my life three things played a crucial part - Khiladi film, Tu Cheez Badi Hai Mast Mast song and Chura Ke Dil Mera song - these three things shaped up my career. This song gave a turning point to my career,” Akshay said.

Akshay Kumar flaunts his dance moves. (IANS)

The song that featured Akshay and Raveena Tandon became one of biggest chartbusters of the 1990s. It has been recreated for Abbas-Mustan’s directorial venture Machine, which marks debut of Abbas Burmawala’s son, Mustafa.

Still got those mast mast moves 😉 What say? #TuCheezBadiHaiMastMast pic.twitter.com/XBS8J4gbrK — Akshay Kumar (@akshaykumar) March 6, 2017

Speaking at the launch the new version of the song, Akshay said, “I did not do any rehearsals. We had the choreographers and we used to rehearsals on the spot. We shot the song in Filmmalaya studio and we had nine cameras shooting the song it was a big thing then.”

Actor Akshay Kumar during the song launch Cheez Badi Hai Mast Mast in Mumbai on March 5. (IANS)

Watch the new version here

The actor scored his first big hit with Abbas-Mustan’s Khiladi and went on to do films like Ajnabee and Aitraaz with them. “Due to Abbas-Mustan I got my first hit film Khiladi and I am grateful to them. I would have done anything for them today.”

Actor Akshay Kumar enjoys himself during the song launch Cheez Badi Hai Mast Mast in Mumbai. (IANS)

Read more

The new version stars Kiara Advani and the actress says she showed the song to the original star Raveena two days before the release. “I showed her the song two days back and she loved it. I wanted to get her blessings. It was surreal to do the song. I used to dance in front of mirror to this song and I got opportunity to do it (dance) in front of camera,” Kiara said.

Akshay Kumar during the song launch. (IANS)

Watch the original song here:

Meanwhile, Akshay also talked about working with Raveena, “It was great honour always working with her. We did so many films together and we had some really good songs as well including Tip Tip Barsa Paani. It’s my favourite song, it was an amazing song.”

